        <updateDate>2011-09-21T15:52:09Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Amends the Internal Revenue Code, with respect to regulations governing&nbsp;the tax deduction for income attributable to domestic production activities, to specify that such regulations shall be written to prevent more than one taxpayer from being allowed a deduction with respect to the same qualified production&nbsp;activities income derived from any activity qualifying for a tax deduction.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>To amend the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 to clarify the domestic production activities deduction rules relating to allowance of deduction by United States contract manufacturers.</title>
